SENATE BILL 326
J2 6lr2208
CF HB 377
By: Senators Lam and Carozza
Introduced and read first time: January 22, 2026
Assigned to: Finance
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Physician Assistants – Parity With Other Health Care Practitioners
3 (Physician Assistant Parity Act of 2026)
4 FOR the purpose of altering certain provisions of law to include physician assistants in the
5 health care practitioners who may take certain actions, including actions related to
6 the guardianship of disabled persons, admission of individuals to mental health
7 facilities, the Emergency and Allergy Treatment Program, and the Attendant Care
8 Program; requiring the Maryland Department of Health to cover charges related to
9 examinations by a physician assistant for certain emergency evaluees; altering the
10 membership and duties of the Statewide Advisory Commission on Immunization;
11 and generally relating to physician assistants.
